Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.76,0:50:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong. You see that what they are doing\Nis they're doing that because they think
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.11,0:51:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the right thing to do. Even if\Nthey think killing you is the right
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.76,0:51:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,thing to do. You can appreciate the fact\Nthat they're doing it for a good reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.16,0:51:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,World War II. I didn't hate the enemy.\NDidn't hate them. And uh they were doing
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.44,0:51:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what they could for the for their own\Ncountry. And um and blowing up our naval
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.72,0:51:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,vessels was part of their uh job.\NAnd sometimes they did a good job of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.55,0:51:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,unfortunately.\NBut I never hated them because I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.59,0:51:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they were doing it for patriotism,\Nfor their country, for honor, for valor.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.40,0:51:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though they were killing us, I\Nrespected them for what they were for
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.00,0:51:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,their integrity.\NAll right, that's Oh my goodness. What
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.44,0:52:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is that?\NWhat is that, sweetheart? How did I get
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.07,0:52:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in here?\NUh, that's the wolf in sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.96,0:52:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolf and sheep's clothing. And u\Nthis is what you'll have to learn to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.28,0:52:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,spot. You have to learn how to spot\Nthe wolf in the sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.24,0:52:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh there are many groups, especially\Npolitical, that promise you all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.92,0:52:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,things. And uh when you uh calibrate\Nthem, you find that they are quite low.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.00,0:52:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Okay. Let's move on to the next\None.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.48,0:52:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Most valuable qualities for a spiritual\Nseeker. All right. We started with start
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.88,0:52:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with the certainty knowing. Just know\Nthat if you're spiritually oriented, you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.96,0:52:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,will make progress.\NStart therefore with a feeling of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.28,0:52:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,security\Nof
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.04,0:53:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of insecurity or self-doubt.\NTell yourself anybody who wants to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.40,0:53:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,evolve spiritually will receive the\Nnecessary assistance and success is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.44,0:53:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,guaranteed.\NUh get rid of self-doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.07,0:53:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,any idea that you're not worth it or\Nyou're not capable of it or that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.88,0:53:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,not the right time in your life. Uh all\Nit's always the right time in your life
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.28,0:53:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,except without reservation that you are\Nworthy of the quest be resolved
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.48,0:53:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to totally surrender to the truth about\NGod.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.44,0:53:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender to the truth about God and\Nthat your spiritual evolution is aligned
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.72,0:53:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with God's will for you. Resist. Um,\Nokay. Move to the next one. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.68,0:53:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Start with a feeling of security instead\Nof self-doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.35,0:54:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The facts that aren't to be unreservedly\Naccepted are simple and very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.35,0:54:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrendering to them brings about a\Npolit spiritual enormous spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.64,0:54:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,progress and advancement.\NOkay, let's go to the next one. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.64,0:54:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The living proof of God's love and will\Nfor you is the gift of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.55,0:54:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\NThe fact that you are
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.88,0:54:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is the best evidence there is of God's\Nlove and will for you. Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.40,0:54:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Other valuable quality qualities for a\Nspiritual seeker. Do not compare
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.68,0:54:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself with others regarding holiness,\Nmerit, goodness, deservingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.11,0:54:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sinlessness.\NDo not compare yourself to others. What
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.76,0:55:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,others are is irrelevant.\NWhat's important is what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.31,0:55:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize\Nthese are all human notions you have
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.16,0:55:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,about being better. And God is not\Nlimited by human notions.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.31,0:55:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that\Nthe concept of the fear of God is
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.04,0:55:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance.\NGod is peace and love and nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.20,0:55:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There a lot of people talk about the\Nfear of God and use God as a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.07,0:55:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\NGod is nothing but love and peace and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.11,0:55:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing else.\NPeople think that they're being punished
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.52,0:55:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,by God and that's not the case. What\Nwhat they're being punished by is their
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.35,0:55:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,lack of uh alignment with divinity.\NRealize that the dep depiction of God as
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.20,0:56:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a judge is a delusion\Nis an ego fixation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.55,0:56:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,arising out of guilt. Realize that God\Nis not a parent. So what what God
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.64,0:56:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes in most people's mind is a\Nparent. Uh rewards you and loves you if
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.48,0:56:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you're good and punishes you if you're\Nbad.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.35,0:56:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's nothing but apparent. So\Nrealize that God is something greater
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.52,0:56:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,than a parent. Amen.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.79,0:56:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ's teaching was essentially and\Nsimply to avoid negativity
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.83,0:56:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nthe purpose of Christianity was to reach
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.59,0:56:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional love.\Ncalibration level 540 and over. So what
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.20,0:57:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ wanted us to reach was\Nunconditional love, unconditional life.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.35,0:57:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ knew that once the level of\Nunconditional love was reached, the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.92,0:57:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,soul's destiny was\Ncertain and the soul was safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.55,0:57:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhhuh.\NThis is a essentially the same teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.83,0:57:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,as the other world world's great\Nreligions such as lotus land Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.55,0:57:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,U\Nsometimes spiritual seekers will become
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.20,0:57:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,confused. Are they following the right\Nteacher? Are they studying with the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.59,0:57:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,right teacher? Are they reading the\Nright books? Are they going to the right
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.72,0:57:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,church? Do they belong to the right\Nreligion? And what you do is you filter
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.16,0:57:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,through them and you see that the\Nessence of all of them is almost
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.55,0:57:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,identical. The essence, not the surface\Nof it, but the essence is almost
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.92,0:57:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,identical. All right?\NRealize that salvation and enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.07,0:58:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,are somewhat different goals.\NSalvation is cons concerned with a yes
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.59,0:58:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or no.\NAnd enlightenment is concerned with uh
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.88,0:58:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming\Nsomething beyond that which you have
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.96,0:58:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,been.\NSalvation requires
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.96,0:58:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,purification of the ego. Enlightenment\Nis concerned with letting it go and
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.92,0:58:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,eliminating the ego.\NThe goal of enlightenment is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.16,0:58:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhat more demanding\Nthan simply being a good person.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.96,0:58:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment is something other than\Ngood personhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.72,0:58:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's advancing one's level of\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.96,0:58:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in the nonlinear realms.\NYes. And the next slide clarify that it
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.24,0:58:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is not a personal you who is seeking\Nenlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.11,0:59:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but rather a quality of consciousness\Nitself that is the motivator.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.68,0:59:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So you like to think of I am this or I\Nam that and actually
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.79,0:59:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's merely consciousness itself\Nuh and being what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.11,0:59:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual inspiration and dedication\Ncarry forth the work within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.11,0:59:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Your own spiritual momentum.\NEverybody here has spiritual momentum or
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.11,0:59:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they wouldn't be here. Anybody who raise\Nanybody who's not here raise your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.72,0:59:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody stand what up. Therefore,\Neverybody in this audience is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.52,0:59:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh we throw all the bad ones out at\Nthe door anyway. We can tell right away
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.64,0:59:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're a deadbeat. And we have a\Nside door that says entrance, but
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.68,1:00:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,actually it's an exit to the alley.\NDead beats this way, enlightened people
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.40,1:00:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,this way. Yes. So our kindness and\Nhumbleness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.52,1:00:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we send them out to exit.\NComfort replaces insecurity when one
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.44,1:00:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,realizes that the most important goal\Nhas already been accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.92,1:00:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal is to be on the path.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.59,1:00:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody here\Nis okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.72,1:00:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you wanted to hear that today. I\Njust
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.52,1:00:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody would be here if they were not\Nspiritually aligned, spiritually
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.16,1:00:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,committed, and spiritually motivated\Nand had a good prognosis. Mhm. Let's see
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.04,1:01:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if there's any dead beats here.\NThis This crowd is 100% okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.88,1:01:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,100%, folks.\NNobody would be here that was not
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.16,1:01:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,destined for enlightenment and as well\Nas not only salvation but enlightened
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.35,1:01:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because nobody else would be here.\NYeah. Nobody'd be in a cookie store if
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.68,1:01:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they didn't want cookies. Okay.\NComfort replaces insecurity. When Ren
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.35,1:01:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,realizes the most important goal has\Nalready been accomplished,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.28,1:01:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the goal is to be on the road to\Nspiritual evolution. Therefore, everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.04,1:01:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in this audience is on the road and is\Nalready successful or they wouldn't be
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.96,1:02:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,here. That's a wonderful thing to know.\NAlso, it's it's sort of good the world's
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.16,1:02:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,not going to end today.\NThere was some clergy in blasting that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.31,1:02:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the world was going to end today, but\Nit's not going to end today. Okay. I
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.68,1:02:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,hate to disappoint anybody, but the\Nworld is not ending today. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.07,1:02:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual love,\Nspiritual development is not an
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.79,1:02:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,accomplishment, but a way of life.\NIt is an orientation that brings its own
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.92,1:02:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,rewards\Nand what is important is the direction
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.68,1:02:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of one's own motives in life. So there's\Nno
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.83,1:02:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh value in keeping a scorecard on\Nyourself. A scorecard, how far have I
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.96,1:02:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,come or how far do other people think I\Nhave come? Uh
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.11,1:02:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the only one you have to answer to is\Nyourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.88,1:03:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And the motivation to seek God is God.\NNo. Nobody seeks God except under the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.68,1:03:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,influence of divinity\Nbecause man left to his own device would
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.72,1:03:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,never think of it. Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.48,1:03:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Appreciate that every step forward\Nbrings benefits to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.31,1:03:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you advance spiritually\Nit brings a value to everyone to every
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.88,1:03:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,human being because of the collective\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.52,1:03:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single person who improves\Nuh helps elevate the level of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.31,1:03:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness and as that elevates the\Nincidence of war, suffering,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.59,1:03:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance, sagging and disease diminish.\NSo when you advance yourself, you are
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.00,1:03:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,helping everybody.\NAppreciate that every step forward
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.24,1:04:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,benefits everyone.\NOnce spiritual dedication at work is a
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.83,1:04:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,gift to life and the love of mankind,\Nit's nice to know that what you think
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.11,1:04:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you're doing only for yourself is\Nactually benefiting everyone around you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.88,1:04:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To be kind to just one living being\Nbenefits everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.68,1:04:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThere is no
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.35,1:04:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,timetable or\Nprescribed
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.92,1:04:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,route to God.\NAlthough each person's route is unique,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.83,1:04:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the terrain to be covered is relatively\Ncommon to all.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.55,1:04:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever torment you go through in\Ntrying to perfect yourself, overcome
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.16,1:04:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,sinfulness and selfishness, etc. Realize\Nthat this is common to all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.28,1:04:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People troop into church Sunday\Nmornings, everybody working on the same
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.40,1:05:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,problem. How to be less selfish, how to\Nbe more giving, how to be more loving,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.59,1:05:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, etc.\NAll right. The work is to surmount and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.59,1:05:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend the common human feelings that\Nare inherent in the structure of the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.31,1:05:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,human ego. So whatever defects you have\Nare not just personal, they're not just
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.03,1:05:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,yours. They are the problem of the human\Nego itself. And the problem is one of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.55,1:05:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution that mankind at this point has\Nevolved to a certain point and that's as
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.64,1:05:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,far as it's gotten as of as of today.\NOne would like to think they are
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.68,1:05:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,personal. However, the ego\Nitself is not personal. People would
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.72,1:05:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,like to think oh me and my progress or\Nme and my sins or me and my
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.96,1:06:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,difficulties. And what you're talking\Nabout is not your personal self. The
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.55,1:06:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,problem is that of the ego itself.\NThe problem is the ego itself. And so
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.40,1:06:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you stop taking the ego personally.\NI blame everything on the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.96,1:06:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the brain that takes the lumps with\Nme.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.76,1:06:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have a way of sort of cajoling\Ninformation out of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.52,1:06:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I speak to it as brain. I say brain. Now\Nyou know who wrote wrote who who wrote
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.07,1:06:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that? I can't think of who wrote it. Uh\Nwho wrote it? Who wrote it? Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.55,1:06:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, and then I asked my brain and I\Nsaid, "If you look a little straight
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.03,1:06:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,ahead and then start it to the right,\Nthere is a neuron over there and if you
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.76,1:06:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,grab it."\NThe tale of two cities. I've been
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.20,1:07:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,grabbing its butt. Who wrote a tale of\Ntwo cities? And I kind of catch it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.55,1:07:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,before it forgets it.\NI forget his name now. Who wrote a tale
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.44,1:07:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of two cities? Let's see.\NUh Dickens, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.72,1:07:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that thought Charles Dickens was a\Nlittle to the right of the central
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.83,1:07:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,vision and over to the right\Nthere's a neuron over there that knows
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.44,1:07:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,everything.\NAnd I look at that neuron and I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.16,1:07:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"What's the name of who wrote that?\NAnd then right away I got Charles
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.68,1:07:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Dickens.\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.31,1:07:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the secret.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.68,1:07:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see that what we like to think\Nthat we are our problem is personal but
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.88,1:08:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really a collective problem that\Nyou share with all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.40,1:08:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and that makes you feel a little less\Nguilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.44,1:08:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the personal self. It's the\Nhuman ego which comes out of the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.72,1:08:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,structure of the brain itself plus the\Nhuman experience of life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.52,1:08:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to surmount and transcend the\Ncommon human feelings that are inherent
